President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to launch the Health Sector Anti-Corruption Forum (HSACF) at the Union Buildings in Pretoria on Tuesday. The Forum is a collaboration between various stakeholders in the fight against fraud and corruption in the health sector. Stakeholders will sign terms of reference outlining the mutual support and cooperation. These include among others the Special Investigating Unit, the National Department of Health, the Council for Medical Schemes, Independent Police Investigative Directorate and Corruption Watch.